entry.title: Revert "[//cc] Add MappableSI path to OneCopyRasterBufferProvider"
entry.content:
This reverts commit 031f7c9ee19d8524abd7a1351b2e10de44ac78bf.



Reason for revert: Might cause a test consistency failure on https://ci.chromium.org/ui/p/chromium/builders/luci.chromium.ci/chromeos-amd64-generic-rel



Apologize for reverting. Please feel free to reland if it is not related, thanks.



Original change's description:

> [//cc] Add MappableSI path to OneCopyRasterBufferProvider

>

> This CL adds a new path to OneCopyRasterBufferProvider that uses

> MappableSharedImage rather than GpuMemoryBuffer. The new path is

> protected by a killswitch. The gist of the change is that rather than

> creating a GpuMemoryBuffer, mapping that in, and then later creating a

> SharedImage from it, the new path directly creates a

> MappableSharedImage (via the new CreateSI() entrypoint), maps that in,

> *and* additionally uses it in the same ways that the SI created from

> the GMB is being used.

>

> One subtlety is that the GMB is created with the size of the

> StagingBuffer, while the SharedImage for the StagingBuffer in its

> current creation point in CopyOnWorkerThread() is created with the

> `resource_size` param passed to PlaybackAndCopyOnWorkerThread(). Thus,

> we would want the MappableSI for the StagingBuffer to be created with

> "both" sizes. Fortunately (and as one would expect), the StagingBuffer

> is initialized with the `resource_size` param, so the two sizes are

> guaranteed to be the same [1].

>

> [1] https://source.chromium.org/chromium/chromium/src/+/main:cc/raster/one_copy_raster_buffer_provider.cc;l=295-297?q=CopyOnWorker&ss=chromium

entry.title: Change GWS ID assignments for 64-bit Clank experiment to M117+, M118+
entry.content:
We still want to be able to start tracking an experiment from a certain

milestone, but we don't want to end it at that same milestone (in case

we want to collect more data).



Note that M117 is already shipping to Stable, but that's ok, no changes

needed there. We have to, however, merge the change into M118 branch

before it hits Stable, so that it also emits the M117+ ID.



While at it, remove the IDs related to M116. We won't use them. The

experiment shipped mid-M116, and we have no way to filter by

sub-milestone version in Rasta, so the results would be a mixed bag of

pre-shipped and post-shipped data.
